oothills%20of%20mountains%20and%20homes%20tucked%20into%20steep%20canyons%20that%20are%20vulnerable%20to%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20suggest%20relocating%20people%20out%20of%20areas%20most%20likely%20to%20burn%2C%20using%20more%20fire-resistant%20materials%2C%20establishing%20bigger%20buffer%20zones%20around%20homes%20and%20neighborhoods%20free%20of%20flammable%20vegetation%20and%20materials%2C%20and%20building%20more%20densely%20in%20safer%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20the%20rebuilding%20effort%20begins%20to%20take%20shape%2C%20orders%20from%20city%20and%20state%20officials%20suggest%20they%20may%20not%20be%20taking%20that%20advice.%20LA%20Mayor%20Karen%20Bass%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmayor.lacity.gov%2Fnews%2Fmayor-bass-issues-sweeping-executive-order-clear-way-angelenos-rebuild-their-homes-fast%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eissued%20an%20executive%20order%20%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20January%2013%20clearing%20the%20way%20to%20%26quot%3Brebuild%20homes%20as%20they%20were.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20states%20that%20to%20be%20eligible%20for%20an%20expedited%20permitting%20process%2C%20a%20home%20must%20be%20rebuilt%20at%20the%20same%20location%20as%20it%20was%20before%20burning%20down%20and%20can't%20be%20converted%20from%20single-family%20to%20multi-family.%20A%20home%20also%20can't%20expand%20its%20footprint%20by%20more%20than%2010%25.%20The%20directives%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecould%20leave%20those%20rebuilt%20homes%20just%20as%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20next%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDetailed%20below%20are%20some%20of%20the%20approaches%20experts%20said%20could%20help%20LA%20rebuild%20more%20safely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b5650151-1812-4aad-a72c-2037d726a1e8%5C%22%3EMoving%20people%20to%20safer%20places%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20Americans%20have%20been%20moving%20into%20communities%20nestled%20next%20to%20and%20within%20forests%20and%20hills.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D92a86309da8af9c28c10ca5b6aa5757a3e91f2f44f8b02e2d254a15f222499c9%26postID%3D678807416f72cdb86149d546%26postSlug%3Dwhat-burned-los-angeles-neighborhoods-can-do-survive-next-fires-2025-1%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41598-022-09707-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20study%20published%20in%20Nature%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%2045%25%20of%20California's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D92a86309da8af9c28c10ca5b6aa5757a3e91f2f44f8b02e2d254a15f222499c9%26postID%3D678807416f72cdb86149d546%26postSlug%3Dwhat-burned-los-angeles-neighborhoods-can-do-survive-next-fires-2025-1%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41598-022-09707-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomes%3C%2Fa%3E%20lie%20in%20those%20areas%2C%20more%20than%20in%20any%20other%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Wara%2C%20director%20of%20the%20climate%20and%20energy%20policy%20program%20at%20the%20Stanford%20Woods%20Institute%20for%20the%20Environment%2C%20said%20incentivizing%20people%20to%20move%20out%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fexperience.arcgis.com%2Fexperience%2F03beab8511814e79a0e4eabf0d3e7247%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethose%20risky%20areas%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20into%20safer%20zones%20%E2%80%94%20or%20managed%20retreat%20%E2%80%94%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20aggressive%20policies%20to%20mitigate%20the%20risk%20of%20wildfires%20and%20other%20disasters.%20The%20idea%20is%20%26quot%3Blargely%20theoretical%26quot%3B%20in%20places%20like%20Pacific%20Palisades%20and%20Aldatena%2C%20he%20added%2C%20in%20part%20because%20they%20had%20vibrant%20economies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20date%2C%20managed%20retreat%20programs%20have%20mostly%20focused%20on%20residents%20in%20a%20few%20flood-prone%20areas%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgrist.org%2Fequity%2Foakwood-beach-staten-island-buyouts-superstorm-sandy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20Staten%20Island%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20Hurricane%20Sandy.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Falaskapublic.org%2Fnews%2F2024-04-22%2Frelocation-of-eroding-alaska-native-village-seen-as-a-test-case%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlaska%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fisledejeancharles.la.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGulf%20Coast%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20communities%20disappearing%20due%20to%20melting%20permafrost%20and%20erosion%20and%20rising%20sea%20levels%2C%20respectively%2C%20were%20relocated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20California%20program%20last%20year%20offered%20up%20to%20%24350%2C000%20in%20forgivable%20loans%20to%20people%20who%20were%20displaced%20by%20fires%20in%202018%20and%202020%20to%20move%20out%20of%20high-hazard%20areas%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgsfahome.org%2Fprograms%2Fdpa%2FReCoverCA.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20the%20funds%20were%20quickly%20depleted%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManaged%20retreat%20is%20often%20%26quot%3Bpolitically%20toxic%2C%26quot%3B%20Stephen%20Smith%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Building%20in%20North%20America%2C%20said.%20Asking%20longtime%20residents%20and%20homeowners%20to%20leave%20their%20properties%20and%20communities%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20just%20redesign%20them%20%E2%80%94%20is%20challenging%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20expensive.%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F01%2F19%2Fopinion%2Flos-angeles-wildfires-burn.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearchers%20also%20warned%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20buyouts%20in%20wildfire-prone%20areas%20could%20make%20the%20problem%20worse%20if%20abandoned%20lots%20become%20piles%20of%20kindling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20alternative%20strategy%20is%20building%20more%20housing%20in%20safer%20parts%20of%20the%20city.%20Most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbelonging.berkeley.edu%2Fsingle-family-zoning-greater-los-angeles%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eof%20the%20greater%20LA%20area%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20dominated%20by%20very%20low-density%2C%20single-family%20detached%20houses.%20Restrictive%20zoning%20that%20prohibited%20multifamily%20buildings%20helped%20encourage%20residential%20sprawl.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20California%20has%20passed%20a%20slew%20of%20laws%20designed%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20build%20more%20dense%20housing.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcalmatters.digitaldemocracy.org%2Fbills%2Fca_202320240sb450%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20state%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20legalizing%20duplexes%20and%20lot-splitting%20in%20single-family%20neighborhoods%20across%20California%20could%20help%20boost%20density%20in%20single-family%20neighborhoods%20in%20LA%20further%20from%20the%20most%20fire-prone%20wilderness%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c33249af-7966-4651-a8e8-0b9386929f30%5C%22%3EMaking%20homes%20and%20neighborhoods%20more%20fire-resistant%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELA%20officials%20should%20be%20considering%20community-wide%20plans%20for%20hardening%20homes%20and%20managing%20vegetation%20in%20yards%20and%20surrounding%20hillsides%2C%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fengineering.oregonstate.edu%2Fpeople%2Ferica-fischer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EErica%20Fischer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20Oregon%20State%20University%20College%20of%20Engineering%20who%20studies%20fire%20resilience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20fires%20can%20easily%20jump%20from%20one%20house%20to%20the%20next%2C%20both%20from%20embers%20carried%20by%20high-speed%20winds%20or%20radiant%20heat%20that%20ignites%20materials%20%E2%80%94%20two%20factors%20that%20caused%20the%20Palisades%20and%20Eaton%20fires%20to%20spread%20so%20fast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20this%20comes%20down%20to%20not%20rebuilding%20quickly%2C%20taking%20the%20time%20to%20really%20make%20a%20community-wide%20plan%2C%20and%20then%20enforcing%20and%20enacting%20that%20plan%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20that%20costs%20money%20and%20is%20daunting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202008%2C%20California%20passed%20some%20of%20the%20strictest%20building%20codes%20in%20the%20country%20for%20homes%20in%20moderate-to-high-risk%20wildfire%20zones.%20They%20mandate%20fire-resistant%20materials%20for%20roofs%2C%20siding%2C%20and%20windows.%20Vents%20must%20have%20screens%20that%20shield%20embers%20from%20entering%20the%20home.%20So-called%20%26quot%3Bdefensible%20space%26quot%3B%20rules%20require%20homeowners%20to%20remove%20flammable%20materials%20like%20trees%20and%20shrubs%20starting%2030%20feet%20from%20the%20edge%20of%20buildings.%20The%20state%20fire%20agency%2C%20CalFire%2C%20also%20has%20the%20authority%20to%20fine%20homeowners%20who%20don't%20follow%20the%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20older%20homes%20account%20for%20a%20large%20portion%20of%20those%20in%20LA%20County%20and%20weren't%20built%20to%20those%20strict%20codes%2C%20which%20added%20to%20the%20devastation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZach%20Seidl%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Bass%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email%20that%20the%20mayor%20wants%20to%20rebuild%20the%20Palisades%20to%20be%20more%20resilient%20but%20didn't%20say%20what%20measures%20she%20was%20considering.%20Seidl%20noted%20that%20current%20building%20codes%20are%20safer%20than%20decades%20ago%20and%20pointed%20to%20Bass'%20strategy%20to%20tackle%20LA's%20affordable%20housing%20crisis%2C%20which%20the%20mayor%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmayor.lacity.gov%2Fnews%2Fdelivering-results-2024-mayor-bass-announces-new-one-year-extension-al-fresco-outdoor-dining%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20spurred%20more%20than%20400%2C000%20new%20housing%3C%2Fa%3E%20units%20across%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20CalFire%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20since%202020%2C%20the%20agency%20has%20funded%20nearly%20%2420%20million%20in%20wildfire%20prevention%20grants%20to%20neighborhoods%20and%20homeowners%20and%20reduced%20fuels%20on%20more%20than%201%2C300%20acres%20in%20LA%20County.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20said%20much%20of%20the%20risk%20stems%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F6046368%2Fwood-steel-houses-fires%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecombustible%20materials%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20namely%20wood%20framing%20%E2%80%94%20most%20American%20single-family%20homes%20are%20built%20with.%20%26quot%3BAn%20urban%20fire%20is%20fueled%20by%20the%20actual%20structures%2C%20and%20we%20build%20our%20structures%20out%20of%20fuel%20in%20America%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20makes%20the%20US%20an%20outlier%2C%20he%20added.%20Many%20countries%20have%20evolved%20to%20rely%20mainly%20on%20concrete%2C%20which%20is%20less%20likely%20to%20catch%20fire.%20The%20abundance%20of%20wood%20construction%20in%20the%20US%20is%20a%20result%20of%20both%20tradition%20and%20the%20lower%20cost%20of%20wood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22137132db-8c1d-4cfe-ae15-f37b1024b97b%5C%22%3EBut%20the%20need%20to%20quickly%20rebuild%20might%20mean%20taking%20the%20path%20of%20least%20resistance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20rebuilding%20efforts%20after%20other%20recent%20fires%20in%20California%20are%20any%20indication%2C%20homes%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Palisades%2C%20Altadena%2C%20and%20elsewhere%20in%20LA%20will%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F11%2F09%2Fus%2Fparadise-fire.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebe%20rebuilt%20in%20more%20fire-resistant%20ways%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0but%20communities%20won't%20be%20designed%20is%20a%20drastically%20different%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELA's%20booming%20economy%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcalmatters.org%2Fhousing%2F2025%2F01%2Fca-wui-housing-policy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacute%20housing%20shortage%3C%2Fa%3E%20intensify%20the%20need%20for%20a%20quick%20recovery.%20Rebuilding%20what%20previously%20existed%20is%20often%20the%20path%20of%20least%20resistance%20after%20disasters%2C%20as%20it's%20easier%20to%20obtain%20the%20necessary%20permits%20and%20homeowners%20may%20be%20cost-limited%20by%20inadequate%20insurance%20payouts%20and%20rising%20construction%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20no%20time%20for%20urban%20planning%20exercising.%20That'll%20delay%20it%20by%2015%20years.%20We%20need%20people%20back%20in%20their%20houses%2C%26quot%3B%20Steve%20Soboroff%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20developer%20and%20former%20police%20commissioner%20tasked%20with%20managing%20the%20city's%20rebuilding%20efforts%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxla.com%2Fvideo%2F1578722%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20at%20a%20news%20conference%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWara%20said%20LA%20officials'%20plans%20are%20setting%20people%20up%20for%20another%20disaster.%20He%20noted%20that%20Pacific%20Palisades%20and%20Altadena%20%E2%80%94%20which%20saw%20some%20of%20the%20worst%20damage%20%E2%80%94%20were%20laid%20out%20decades%20ago%20without%20wildfires%20in%20mind.%20Winding%20roads%20head%20toward%20the%20coast%20and%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20the%20powerful%20Santa%20Ana%20winds%20that%20blow%20flames%20from%20east%20to%20west%20into%20densely%20populated%20towns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClimate%20change%20is%20only%20making%20catastrophic%20wildfires%20more%20likely%2C%20Wara%20added.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20LA%20saw%20record%20rainfall%20and%20abundant%20vegetation.%20Then%20last%20year%2C%20during%20a%20scorching%20hot%20summer%2C%20it%20quickly%20dried%20up%2C%20setting%20the%20stage%20for%20the%20current%20wildfires.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.ucla.edu%2Freleases%2Ffloods-droughts-fires-hydroclimate-whiplash-speeding-up-globally%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%20by%20UCLA%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20rising%20global%20temperatures%20are%20making%20this%20kind%20of%20%26quot%3Bwhiplash%26quot%3B%20between%20rain%20and%20drought%20more%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20disaster%20like%20the%20fires%20in%20LA%2C%20there's%20enormous%20pressure%20on%20political%20leaders%20to%20rebuild%20affected%20communities%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible.%20And%20that%20crunch%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20elevated%20costs%20that%20come%20with%20surging%20demand%20for%20construction%20resources%20%E2%80%94%20might%20not%20leave%20time%20for%20rethinking%20how%20the%20rebuilding%20happens%20to%20better%20protect%20communities%20going%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20would%20think%20this%20would%20be%20an%20opportunity%20to%20harden%20the%20properties%2C%20to%20maybe%20not%20build%20on%20some%20lots%20that%20were%20immediately%20in%20the%20wildland%20interface.%20But%20what%20we%20see%20time%20and%20time%20again%20is%20the%20political%20realities%20going%20in%20exactly%20the%20opposite%20direction%2C%26quot%3B%20Ben%20Metcalf%2C%20a%20housing%20policy%20researcher%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20the%20affected%20communities%20will%20likely%20be%20built%20back%20to%20look%20much%20as%20they%20did%20before%20the%20fires.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20left%20with%20the%20same%20strategy%20we've%20got%2C%20just%20a%20little%20beefier%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-burned-los-angeles-neighborhoods-can-do-survive-next-fires-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737795961000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678a8504ae09223df2ba70dc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-burned-los-angeles-neighborhoods-can-do-survive-next-fires-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Experts%20in%20fire%20mitigation%20and%20climate%20science%20said%20LA%20should%20use%20the%20fires%20as%20an%20opportunity%20to%20design%20more%20resilient%20communities.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman%2CCatherine%20Boudreau)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-burned-los-angeles-neighborhoods-can-do-survive-next-fires-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Trump%20and%20GOP%20lawmakers%20may%20have%20in%20store%20for%20student-loan%20borrowers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20collage%20featuring%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20US%20Capitol%20building%20dome%2C%20and%20rearview%20of%20Graduate%20in%20cap%20and%20gown%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6793b8f910c98eace913cbca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0%3Cp%3EKevin%20Dietsch%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGOP%20lawmakers%20compiled%20a%20list%20of%20ideas%20to%20help%20shape%20the%20budget%20this%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20ideas%20included%20rescinding%20Biden's%20student-debt%20relief%20efforts%2C%20including%20the%20SAVE%20plan.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERepublicans%20have%20also%20proposed%20ideas%20that%20have%20bipartisan%20support%2C%20like%20ending%20interest%20capitalization.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20the%20new%20Republican-controlled%20Congress%20could%20make%20major%20changes%20for%20millions%20of%20student-loan%20borrowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20new%20GOP%20trifecta%20is%20likely%20to%20unwind%20several%20of%20former%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20moves%20on%20student%20debt%20relief.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20memo%20compiled%20by%20Republicans%20on%20the%20House%20Budget%20Committee%20and%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%20put%20forth%20a%20list%20of%20options%20that%20included%20changes%20to%20education%20programs%20that%20could%20appear%20in%20a%20coming%20spending%20bill.%20It%20suggested%20repealing%20Biden's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsave-plan-blocked-student-loan-borrowers-cheaper-payments-debt-cancellation-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESAVE%20income-driven%20repayment%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20repealing%20regulations%20that%20allowed%20for%20debt%20relief%20for%20defrauded%20borrowers%2C%20and%20limiting%20eligibility%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-pslf-borrowers-getting-debt-cancellation-biden-relief-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPublic%20Service%20Loan%20Forgiveness%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20memo%20also%20proposed%20allowing%20borrowers%20who%20default%20on%20their%20student%20loans%20to%20be%20eligible%20for%20a%20second%20%26quot%3Brehabilitation%20loan%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20would%20allow%20borrowers%20to%20exit%20default%20by%20making%20nine%20payments.%20The%20law%20only%20allows%20borrowers%20to%20rehabilitate%20their%20loans%20once.%20It%20also%20suggested%20reforming%20the%20Pell%20Grant%20to%20expand%20its%20eligibility%20to%20short-term%20credential%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20separate%20budget%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbudget.house.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2Freverse_the_curse_budget_blueprint_fy25-341.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblueprint%3C%2Fa%3E%20prepared%20by%20GOP%20members%20on%20the%20budget%20committee%20pledged%20to%20stop%20Biden's%20%26quot%3Bstudent%20loan%20bailout%2C%26quot%3B%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Bour%20budget%20resolution%20stops%20all%20forms%20of%20these%20unconstitutional%2C%20inflationary%2C%20and%20regressive%20student%20loan%20debt%20cancellations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden%20concluded%20his%20term%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-final-student-loan-forgiveness-action-debt-relief-borrowers-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinal%20week%20of%20targeted%20student-debt%20relief%3C%2Fa%3E%20measures%20for%20borrowers.%20He%20announced%20targeted%20relief%20for%20thousands%20of%20nonprofit%20and%20government%20workers%2C%20those%20with%20total%20and%20permanent%20disabilities%2C%20and%20those%20the%20Education%20Department%20found%20were%20defrauded%20by%20their%20schools%2C%20bringing%20total%20relief%20under%20Biden%20to%20%24188.8%20billion%20for%205.3%20million%20borrowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Education%20Department%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%20on%20Trump's%20priorities%20for%20higher%20education%20and%20student-loan%20borrowers.%20However%2C%20Trump%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsave-plan-cheaper-student-loan-payments-trump-debt-relief-biden-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20been%20critical%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Biden's%20debt%20relief%20efforts%2C%20and%20it's%20likely%20his%20administration%20would%20support%20GOP%20legislation%20to%20curb%20Biden's%20expanded%20relief%20and%20repayment%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERep.%20Tim%20Walberg%2C%20chair%20of%20the%20House%20education%20committee%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20he%20remains%20%26quot%3Bcommitted%20to%20helping%20address%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20college%20tuition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRepublicans%20are%20committed%20to%20pursuing%20policies%20that%20will%20lower%20the%20cost%20of%20college%20and%20protect%20students%20and%20taxpayers%20from%20colleges%20and%20universities%20that%20offer%20degrees%20that%20aren't%20worth%20the%20cost%2C%26quot%3B%20Walberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224e3fa680-960f-4ea8-be2f-8f68efad469b%5C%22%3EGOP%20higher%20education%20plans%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GOP%20memo%20said%20that%20eliminating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-debt-borrowers-apply-income-driven-repayment-save-plan-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20SAVE%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20streamlining%20other%20income-driven%20repayment%20plans%20would%20save%20%24127.3%20billion%20over%20a%20decade.%20The%20SAVE%20plan%2C%20first%20introduced%20in%202023%2C%20was%20intended%20to%20make%20monthly%20student-loan%20payments%20cheaper%20with%20a%20shorter%20timeline%20for%20loan%20forgiveness.%20The%20plan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsave-plan-blocked-student-loan-company-mohela-debt-cancellation-biden-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efaced%20lawsuits%20from%20GOP-led%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20enrolled%20borrowers%20are%20on%20forbearance%20as%20they%20await%20a%20final%20court%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepealing%20Biden's%20regulations%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20borrowers%20who%20the%20government%20determined%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-art-institutes-borrower-defense-debt-cancellation-biden-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edefrauded%20by%20their%20colleges%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20loan%20forgiveness%20is%20also%20among%20the%20GOP's%20suggestions.%20The%20memo%20said%20this%20would%20save%20a%20total%20of%20%2414.6%20billion%20over%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20memo%20proposed%20ending%20interest%20capitalization%2C%20which%20is%20when%20unpaid%20interest%20is%20tacked%20onto%20a%20borrower's%20principal%20balance%2C%20causing%20their%20overall%20debt%20load%20to%20surge.%20This%20is%20an%20idea%20that%20Democratic%20lawmakers%20have%20voiced%20support%20for%2C%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20these%20ideas%20have%20been%20previously%20floated%20in%20GOP%20legislation.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgop-bill-overhaul-student-loan-repayment-stop-debt-relief-foxx-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20College%20Cost%20Reduction%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20introduced%20by%20GOP%20Rep.%20Virgini