g%20the%20industry%20standard%2C%20using%20it%20like%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20other%20tech%20workers%20do%20%E2%80%94%20to%20collaborate%20on%20coding%20projects%20with%20colleagues%2C%20or%20to%20show%20a%20portfolio%20of%20work%20to%20prospective%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20interviewed%20for%20the%20job%20at%20Opal%20Labs%2C%20a%20downtown%20marketing-tech%20firm%2C%20he%20sent%20an%20executive%20his%20GitHub%20profile%20to%20provide%20a%20sample%20of%20code%20he'd%20written.%20Once%20he%20started%20as%20a%20lead%20enterprise%20engineer%2C%20he%20followed%20his%20new%20colleagues'%20lead%20and%20published%20code%20to%20his%20public%20profile%2C%20using%20the%20tool%20to%20keep%20his%20manager%20apprised%20of%20his%20progress.%20When%20he%20left%20the%20company%20six%20months%20later%2C%20Robillard%20again%20used%20GitHub%20as%20part%20of%20his%20job%20hunt%20%E2%80%94%20recreating%20from%20memory%20a%20project%20he'd%20worked%20on%20at%20Opal%20derived%20from%20decades-old%20public%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Opal's%20lawyers%20were%20saying%20that%20code%20Robillard%20had%20posted%20to%20the%20platform%20amounted%20to%20confidential%20trade%20secrets.%20It%20was%20the%20warning%20shot%20in%20what%20would%20become%20a%20four-year%20legal%20nightmare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%2C%20things%20soured%20for%20Robillard%20just%20a%20month%20after%20he%20joined%20the%20company%2C%20when%20he%20invited%20some%20of%20his%20new%20coworkers%20to%20his%2042nd%20birthday%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfterward%2C%20he%20felt%20office%20attitudes%20shift.%20As%20at%20many%20tech%20firms%2C%20Opal's%20workforce%20skewed%20young%3B%20newly%20aware%20of%20his%20age%2C%20colleagues%20now%20called%20him%20%26quot%3Bold%20Greg%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20later%20testified%2C%20and%20the%20CEO%20mocked%20his%20use%20of%20Facebook%20as%20something%20%26quot%3Bolder%20people%26quot%3B%20did.%20He%20also%20said%20he%20heard%20a%20job%20applicant%20dismissed%20as%20%26quot%3Bsome%20old%20guy%20in%20his%2040s.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202015%2C%20after%20Robillard%20missed%20a%20scheduled%20meeting%20with%20a%20client%20without%20alerting%20his%20colleagues%20%E2%80%94%20he%20said%20he%20was%20looking%20after%20his%20son%20as%20his%20wife%20was%20leaving%20town%20for%20a%20funeral%20%E2%80%94%20he%20was%20fired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20spot%20illustration%20of%20a%20man%20walking%20in%20isolation%20amongst%20shadows.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67915f192fcded5e9074568b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETara%20Anand%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOpal%20told%20Robillard%20he%20was%20terminated%20for%20the%20absence%20and%20other%20performance%20issues%2C%20but%20Robillard%20recalled%20colleagues%20missing%20meetings%20without%20consequence.%20He%20started%20wondering%20if%20he'd%20crossed%20an%20invisible%20barrier%20%E2%80%94%20he'd%20become%20%3Cem%3Eold%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20without%20even%20noticing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20had%20been%20discriminated%20against.%20He%20hired%20an%20employment%20lawyer%20and%2C%20about%20a%20year%20after%20his%20termination%2C%20filed%20suit%20against%20Opal%20alleging%20age%20discrimination%2C%20among%20other%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpal's%20lawyers%20filed%20a%20response%20denying%20his%20allegations%2C%20and%20the%20parties%20began%20discovery.%20That's%20when%20the%20company%20fired%20back%20with%20the%20letter%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20countersuit%20against%20Robillard%2C%20accusing%20him%20of%20violating%20state%20and%20federal%20laws%20protecting%20trade%20secrets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuddenly%20he%20was%20being%20cast%20not%20as%20a%20victim%20of%20discrimination%2C%20but%20as%20an%20intellectual%20property%20thief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20horrifying%2C%26quot%3B%20Robillard%20said%20in%20an%20interview.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20using%20this%20pressure%2C%20this%20lever%20that%20I%20hadn't%20even%20thought%20about%20before.%20And%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20very%20upside-down%20experience.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Business%20Insider%20has%20found%2C%20companies%20large%20and%20small%20are%20wielding%20trade%20secrets%20law%20as%20a%20potent%20legal%20strategy%20against%20workers%20who%20have%20accused%20them%20of%20wrongdoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20the%20aerospace%20employee%20who%20was%20laid%20off%20after%20accusing%20colleagues%20of%20Islamophobic%20abuse%3B%20he%20filed%20a%20discrimination%20claim%20and%20was%20then%20countersued%20over%20documents%20he'd%20emailed%20himself%20while%20on%20the%20job.%20There%20was%20the%20music%20school%20director%20who%20said%20he%20was%20subjected%20to%20sexual%20harassment%20and%20a%20hostile%20work%20environment%20and%20was%20sued%20after%20leaving%20to%20start%20a%20rival%20business.%20And%20there%20was%20the%20healthcare%20worker%20who%20was%20fired%20after%20raising%20suspicions%20of%20Medicare%20fraud%20and%20sued%20her%20employer%2C%20alleging%20retaliation%2C%20only%20to%20be%20countersued%20over%20the%20documents%20she%20had%20taken%20to%20substantiate%20her%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20trade%20secret%20law%20to%20fend%20off%20worker%20complaints%20is%20so%20far%20a%20niche%20strategy.%20In%20interviews%2C%20some%20attorneys%20said%20they'd%20never%20seen%20it%20deployed.%20But%20others%20have%20witnessed%20it%20multiple%20times%20and%20said%20its%20use%20was%20on%20the%20upswing.%20Employment%20law%20attorneys%20said%20its%20rise%20has%20been%20aided%20by%20a%20recent%20federal%20law%2C%20a%20shift%20to%20remote%20work%20that%20blurred%20personal%20and%20professional%20boundaries%2C%20and%20a%20growing%20corporate%20surveillance%20culture%20in%20which%20a%20worker's%20every%20action%20can%20be%20tracked%20and%20weaponized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20workers%20were%20sued%20after%20gathering%20evidence%20of%20perceived%20wrongdoing%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20what%20some%20attorneys%20call%20%26quot%3Bself-help%20discovery%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20despite%20whistleblower%20protections%20in%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20cases%2C%20what%20workers%20described%20as%20run-of-the-mill%20professional%20activities%20were%20reframed%20as%20trade%20secret%20misappropriation%3A%20documents%20printed%20out%20to%20review%20at%20home%2C%20a%20work%20email%20forwarded%20to%20a%20personal%20account%20for%20safekeeping%2C%20a%20computer%20shared%20with%20a%20romantic%20partner%2C%20a%20password%20sent%20to%20a%20colleague%20for%20an%20urgent%20task%20%E2%80%94%20or%20code%20saved%20to%20a%20GitHub%20profile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTools%20that%20were%20intended%20to%20help%20businesses%20protect%20themselves%20against%20other%20businesses%20and%20corporate%20espionage%20are%20now%20used%20by%20corporations%20against%20their%20own%20employees%2C%20to%20protect%20the%20company%20at%20all%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jennifer%20Gibson%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20Psst%2C%20a%20whistleblower-support%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EA%20beverage%20company's%20secret%20recipe.%20An%20innovative%20manufacturing%20process.%20A%20social%20media%20platform's%20proprietary%20feed%20algorithm.%20A%20sales%20team's%20closely%20guarded%20customer%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimply%20put%2C%20a%20trade%20secret%20is%20a%20valuable%2C%20proprietary%20piece%20of%20business%20information%20that%20a%20company%20has%20taken%20steps%20to%20keep%20under%20wraps.%20Allowing%20businesses%20to%20safeguard%20information%2C%20processes%2C%20prototypes%2C%20code%2C%20and%20other%20secrets%20from%20rivals%20is%20foundational%20to%20corporate%20law.%20Long%20governed%20by%20the%20states%2C%20the%20law%20was%20fully%20codified%20at%20the%20federal%20level%20in%202016%2C%20when%20President%20Barack%20Obama%20signed%20legislation%20called%20the%20Defend%20Trade%20Secrets%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20legislation%20didn't%20depart%20radically%20from%20existing%20trade%20secrets%20laws%20in%20the%20states%2C%20but%20it%20created%20a%20single%2C%20nationwide%20framework.%20It%20also%20made%20it%20far%20easier%20for%20companies%20to%20bring%20trade%20secrets%20claims%20in%20federal%20courts%2C%20which%20are%20perceived%20by%20many%20attorneys%20as%20favorable%20to%20companies%2C%20in%20part%20because%20of%20stricter%20rules%20and%20faster-moving%20dockets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20spot%20illustration%20showing%20a%20mans%20phone%20with%20a%20reflection%20of%20two%20men%20shaking%20hands.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6791606710c98eace913886f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETara%20Anand%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20both%20state%20and%20federal%20law%2C%20a%20trade%20secret%20has%20been%20misappropriated%20if%20it%20was%20acquired%20or%20disclosed%20without%20consent%20or%20through%20improper%20means%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20or%20not%20it%20made%20its%20way%20to%20a%20rival%20firm.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20matter%20at%20all%20if%20it%20went%20to%20a%20competitor%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Michael%20Risch%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20law%20at%20Villanova%20University.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20obtain%20information%20that%20you're%20not%20entitled%20to%20have%2C%20then%20potentially%20you%20can%20be%20liable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20now%20being%20deployed%20by%20employers%20facing%20claims%20of%20discrimination%20or%20wrongdoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttorneys%20who%20represent%20workers%20in%20employment%20lawsuits%20often%20agree%20to%20take%20a%20case%20on%20contingency%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20they%20bear%20the%20legal%20costs%20and%20are%20paid%20only%20if%20they%20win%20or%20settle.%20But%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20defending%20a%20retaliatory%20counterclaim%2C%20many%20require%20their%20clients%20to%20pay%20up%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20cases%20are%20expensive%3A%20Determining%20whether%20any%20particular%20piece%20of%20information%20is%20a%20trade%20secret%20is%20a%20fact-intensive%20question%20that%20must%20be%20decided%20by%20a%20court%20or%20arbitrator%2C%20an%20often%20time-consuming%20and%20costly%20prospect.%20A%20survey%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aipla.org%2Fdetail%2Fjournal-issue%2F2023-report-of-the-economic-survey%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Intellectual%20Property%20Law%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20in%202022%2C%20the%20median%20cost%20of%20litigating%20a%20trade%20secret%20case%20with%20less%20than%20%241%20million%20at%20stake%20was%20%24750%2C000.%20(Cases%20that%20don't%20make%20it%20to%20trial%2C%20the%20survey%20found%2C%20could%20still%20run%20to%20tens%20or%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoth%20potential%20reputational%20costs%20of%20having%20that%20fight%20happening%20in%20court%2C%20and%20a%20legal%20bill%20an%20ordinary%20person%20simply%20couldn't%20afford%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chris%20Seaman%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Washington%20and%20Lee%20School%20of%20Law%2C%20mean%20%26quot%3Bthe%3Cem%3E%20in%20terrorem%3C%2Fem%3E%20effect%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20fear%20factor%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bwould%20be%20very%20significant.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20any%20trade%20secret%20case%2C%20the%20odds%20are%20strongly%20against%20the%20defendant%3A%20A%20study%20by%20the%20legal%20analytics%20firm%20Lex%20Machina%20of%20all%20trade%20secret%20cases%20in%20US%20District%20Courts%20from%202021%20to%202023%20found%20that%20plaintiffs%20prevailed%20four%20times%20as%20often%20as%20defendants.%20Mostly%2C%20the%20cases%20settled.%20For%20an%20employee%2C%20a%20settlement%20might%20entail%20abandoning%20their%20discrimination%20or%20whistleblower%20claim%2C%20accepting%20a%20smaller%20payout%2C%20or%20even%20paying%20damages%20to%20their%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDid%20all%20these%20lawyers%20go%20to%20a%20conference%20we%20didn't%20hear%20about%3F%26quot%3B%20asked%20Jack%20Moran%2C%20a%20Cleveland%20attorney%20who%20has%20represented%20multiple%20clients%20who%20were%20accused%20of%20trade%20secret%20misappropriation%20after%20raising%20their%20own%20claims%20of%20corporate%20wrongdoing.%20%26quot%3BJust%20one%20after%20the%20other%20is%20adopting%3A%20'The%20best%20defense%20is%20a%20good%20offense%2C'%20even%20if%20the%20employer%20doesn't%20have%20particularly%20viable%20claims.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20examined%20dozens%20of%20federal%20trade%20secrets%20claims%20filed%20by%20companies%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20against%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20who%20also%20had%20filed%20a%20claim%20against%20their%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20suit%20was%20filed%20by%20the%20United%20States%20Olympic%20%26amp%3B%20Paralympic%20Committee.%20Despite%20a%20dearth%20of%20competitors%20%E2%80%94%20the%20committee%20is%20the%20sole%20entity%20responsible%20for%20overseeing%20Team%20USA%20%E2%80%94%20the%20committee%20filed%20a%20trade%20secrets%20claim%20against%20a%20former%20executive%20after%20he%20reported%20allegations%20of%20wrongdoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBill%20Moreau%2C%20a%20chiropractor%2C%20was%20promoted%20by%20the%20committee%20to%20vice%20president%20of%20sports%20medicine%20in%202017.%20Throughout%202018%20and%202019%2C%20he%20repeatedly%20flagged%20what%20he%20said%20were%20troubling%20issues%2C%20according%20to%20court%20filings%3A%20first%2C%20a%20statutory%20rape%20claim%20involving%20a%2015-year-old%20Paralympic%20athlete%3B%20and%20later%2C%20what%20he%20said%20were%20violations%20of%20athletes'%20confidential%20medical%20records%20and%20failures%20of%20care%20for%20athletes%20with%20suicidal%20thoughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202019%2C%20he%20was%20fired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Olympic%20committee%20said%20Moreau%20was%20terminated%20so%20the%20organization%20could%20replace%20him%20with%20someone%20who%20had%20a%20doctor%20of%20medicine%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20doctor%20of%20chiropractic.%20But%20Moreau%20believed%20he%20was%20fired%20in%20retaliation%20for%20what%20he%20described%20as%20whistleblower%20complaints.%20He%20sued%20the%20following%20year%20alleging%20wrongful%20discharge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20approach%20to%20document%20handling%20soon%20made%20him%20a%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20time%20to%20time%2C%20he%20had%20emailed%20himself%20documents%20%E2%80%94%20he%20said%20he'd%20done%20so%20to%20facilitate%20remote%20work%2C%20as%20he%20preferred%20his%20personal%20computer's%20large%20screen%20%E2%80%94%20or%20printed%20them%20out%20and%20took%20them%20home.%20His%20lawyers%20said%20in%20court%20filings%20that%20this%20was%20common%20practice%20among%20the%20committee's%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20also%20saved%20documents%20to%20use%20in%20his%20push%20for%20reform%20at%20the%20committee%20and%20to%20protect%20himself%20from%20becoming%20a%20%26quot%3Bscapegoat.%26quot%3B%20After%20his%20termination%2C%20he%20let%20his%20attorneys%20review%20some%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20the%20Olympic%20committee's%20attorneys%2C%20his%20actions%20were%20grounds%20for%20a%20countersuit%20alleging%20trade%20secret%20misappropriation%3A%20they%20accused%20him%20of%20seeking%20to%20profit%20from%20the%20documents%20and%20said%20his%20actions%20damaged%20the%20committee's%20relationship%20with%20athletes.%20The%20case%20ground%20on%20for%20three%20years%20before%20reaching%20a%20settlement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Moreau's%20attorneys%2C%20Michael%20Fairhurst%2C%20said%20he'd%20noticed%20that%20%26quot%3Bemployers%20are%20becoming%20more%20aggressive%20in%20lodging%20complaints%20of%20misappropriation%20and%20the%20like%20against%20workers%20who%20have%20blown%20the%20whistle%20on%20corruption%2C%20discrimination%2C%20or%20other%20misconduct.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20cases%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bcan%20often%20crush%20employees%20into%20silence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20cases%20BI%20reviewed%2C%20misappropriation%20allegations%20weren't%20just%20deployed%20as%20a%20defense%20maneuver%20after%20an%20employee%20sued.%20In%20many%20instances%2C%20employers%20sued%20aggrieved%20employees%20proactively%20under%20trade%20secrets%20law%20%E2%80%94%20putting%20workers%20on%20the%20backfoot%20from%20the%20get-go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20cases%20hinged%20on%20methods%20of%20forensic%20document%20accounting%20that%20didn't%20exist%20just%20a%20few%20decades%20ago.%20Software%20can%20now%20track%20every%20keystroke%20or%20file%20opened%20during%20a%20worker's%20time%20with%20a%20company%3B%20every%20message%20and%20email%20can%20be%20retained%20for%20posterity.%20When%20someone%20speaks%20out%20against%20an%20employer%2C%20this%20entire%20digital%20history%20can%20be%20scrutinized%20for%20use%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEric%20Bachman%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Bachman%20Law%2C%20in%20Bethesda%2C%20Maryland%2C%20said%20he%20had%20begun%20checking%20whether%20prospective%20clients%20%E2%80%94%20deliberately%20or%20inadvertently%20%E2%80%94%20retained%20any%20files%20from%20their%20employment%2C%20to%20head%20off%20this%20line%20of%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGenerally%20speaking%2C%20you%20just%20want%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20the%20issue%20because%20we%20know%20now%20that%20companies%20are%20being%20more%20aggressive%20about%20pursuing%20these%20claims%26quot%3B%20over%20trade%20secrets%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20various%20types%20of%20legal%20claims%20companies%20can%20make%20against%20workers%2C%20misappropriation%20allegations%20can%20be%20particularly%20damaging%20to%20an%20employee's%20professional%20reputation%2C%20Bachman%20said%2C%20because%20companies%20will%20often%20say%20employees%20%26quot%3Bstole%26quot%3B%20proprietary%20information%20or%20accuse%20them%20of%20%26quot%3Btheft.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20meant%20to%2C%20and%20does%2C%20sound%20like%20the%20employee%20committed%20a%20crime%20of%20some%20sort%2C%26quot%3B%20Bachman%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20is%20a%20far%20different%20implication%20than%20something%20more%20benign-sounding%20like%20breach%20of%20contract.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Defend%20Trade%20Secrets%20Act%20was%20being%20drafted%2C%20its%20authors%20were%20attuned%20to%20how%20it%20might%20be%20abused%20and%20attempted%20a%20remedy%3A%20a%20whistleblower%20immunity%20provision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20clause%20sought%20to%20protect%20workers%20who%20take%20documents%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20prove%20that%20their%20employer%20was%20engaged%20in%20illegal%20activity%2C%20offering%20them%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20for%20what%20might%20otherwise%20constitute%20misappropriation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20provision%20is%20narrowly%20defined%2C%20applying%20only%20to%20workers%20who%20took%20documents%20for%20the%20sole%20purpose%20of%20sharing%20them%20with%20their%20attorneys%20or%20a%20government%20agency.%20That%20means%20employees%20who%20seek%20to%20expose%20discrimination%20or%20wrongdoing%20who%20preserve%20documents%20in%20other%20ways%20%E2%80%94%20by%20sharing%20them%20with%20the%20media%2C%20say%2C%20or%20seeking%20guidance%20from%20a%20confidant%20%E2%80%94%20may%20be%20left%20unprotected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20often%20have%20whistleblowers%20who%20are%20having%20to%20make%20decisions%20in%20less%20than%20ideal%20circumstances%2C%20when%20they%20may%20be%20emotionally%20impacted%20from%20what's%20happening%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gibson%2C%20the%20whistleblower%20advocate.%20%26quot%3BThose%20aren't%20circumstances%20that%20lead%20to%20the%20best%20decision-making.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20practice%2C%20the%20provision%20has%20sometimes%20failed%20to%20protect%20even%20the%20most%20fastidious%20would-be%20whistleblowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20spot%20illustration%20of%20a%20%20backpack%20with%20documents%20spilling%20out%20of%20it.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67915d14ae09223df2bb1bca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETara%20Anand%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20the%20earliest%20cases%20to%20test%20the%20law%2C%20an%20insurance%20company%2C%20Unum%2C%20sued%20a%20former%20employee%2C%20Timothy%20Loftus%2C%20alleging%20misappropriation%20after%20he%20took%20boxes%20of%20documents%20to%20investigate%20what%20he%20suspected%20was%20illegal%20activity.%20The%20worker%20invoked%20the%20whistleblower%20exemption%2C%20but%20the%20judge%20rejected%20the%20motion%2C%20saying%20it%20wasn't%20clear%20that%20Loftus%20took%20the%20documents%20%3Cem%3Esolely%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20investigating%20whether%20a%20crime%20had%20taken%20place.%20(The%20case%20was%20later%20settled.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Menell%2C%20a%20UC%20Berkeley%20law%20professor%20who%20was%20a%20key%20architect%20of%20the%20exemption%2C%20found%20the%20court's%20interpretation%20outrageous.%20In%20a%20January%202017%20research%20paper%2C%20he%20warned%20that%20under%20this%20reading%20of%20the%20law%2C%20%26quot%3Bany%20trade%20secret%20owner%20can%20require%20a%20whistleblower%20to%20defend%20a%20trade%20secret%20lawsuit%20merely%20by%20alleging%20that%20there%20is%20a%20dispute%20over%20the%20employee's%20motivation%20for%20providing%20trade%20secret%20documents%20to%20their%20attorney.%26quot%3B%20Unum%20was%20happier%20with%20the%20outcome%3B%20Emily%20Downing-Baer%2C%20a%20company%20spokesperson%2C%20said%20the%20decision%20demonstrated%20%26quot%3Bthe%20value%20of%20the%20Defend%20Trade%20Secrets%20Act.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20Georgia%20case%20appeared%20to%20be%20exactly%20what%20the%20whistleblower%20exemption%20was%20designed%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristopher%20Young%20had%20suspected%20his%20employer%2C%20an%20Alpharetta-headquartered%20cement%20company%20named%20Argos%2C%20was%20engaged%20in%20illegal%20price-fixing%20%E2%80%94%20coordinating%20with%20competitors%20to%20inflate%20cement%20and%20concrete%20prices%20for%20government%20projects.%20He%20photographed%20and%20secreted%20home%20extensive%20paper%20documents%20to%20support%20his%20suspicions%20and%20used%20them%20as%20the%20basis%20for%20a%20qui%20tam%20lawsuit%20%E2%80%94%20a%20suit%20brought%20by%20a%20private%20citizen%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20US%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYoung%20filed%20his%20qui%20tam%20case%20anonymously%2C%20but%20after%20company%20officials%20discovered%20he%20was%20behind%20it%2C%20Argos%20sued%20him%20in%202018%2C%20alleging%20trade%20secret%20violations.%20The%20company%20claimed%20that%20not%20all%20the%20documents%20Young%20took%20were%20related%20to%20his%20qui%20tam%20lawsuit%20and%20that%20he%20gave%20the%20documents%20to%20a%20competitor.%20Young's%20attorney%20moved%20to%20have%20the%20case%20dismissed%20under%20the%20whistleblower%20clause.%20The%20judge%20denied%20the%20motion%2C%20citing%20Loftus%2C%20even%20as%20she%20agreed%20with%20Young's%20argument%20that%20Argos%20had%20provided%20no%20plausible%20evidence%20that%20he%20had%20disclosed%20trade%20secrets%20to%20another%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20turned%20out%20Young's%20whistleblower%20claims%20had%20merit.%20In%202021%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fopa%2Fpr%2Fready-mix-concrete-company-admits-fixing-prices-and-rigging-bids-violation-antitrust-laws%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20prosecutors%20charged%20Argos%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20price-fixing%20and%20antitrust%20behavior%2C%20which%20the%20company%20admitted%2C%20agreeing%20to%20pay%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fopa%2Fpr%2Fready-mix-concrete-company-admits-fixing-prices-and-rigging-bids-violation-antitrust-laws%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Antitrust%2520Division%2520also%2520announced%2Cthe%2520Antitrust%2520Division%2527s%2520ongoing%2520criminal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2420%20million%20criminal%20penalty%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20cooperate%20with%20the%20ongoing%20investigation.%20Argos'%20case%20against%20Young%20was%20halted%20only%20when%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice's%20antitrust%20division%20intervened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20without%20whistleblower%20status%2C%20it%20is%20illegal%20for%20a%20company%20to%20retaliate%20against%20someone%20who%20engages%20in%20protected%20activity%2C%20such%20as%20filing%20a%20complaint%20over%20gender%20or%20racial%20discrimination.%20But%20again%20and%20again%2C%20courts%20have%20ruled%20that%20trade%20secrets%20claims%20were%20not%20tantamount%20to%20retaliation%20unless%20a%20defendant%20could%20prove%20they%20were%20unreasonable%2C%20%26quot%3Bbaseless%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bfrivolous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%202018%20case%20that%20made%20it%20to%20the%206th%20Circuit%20Court%20of%20Appeals%2C%20an%20Ohio%20insurance%20worker%2C%20Steven%20Aday%2C%20was%20sued%20over%20claims%20of%20trade%20secrets%20violations%20after%20he%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20accusing%20a%20former%20employer%2C%20Westfield%20Insurance%2C%20of%20age%20discrimination.%20At%20issue%20was%20the%20fact%20that%20he'd%20emailed%20himself%20documents%3B%20even%20though%20he%20said%20the%20company%20knew%20other%20employees%20had%20done%20the%20same%20thing%2C%20his%20claim%20of%20retaliation%20was%20rejected%20in%20court.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20many%20reasons%20an%20employer%20would%20not%20litigate%20every%20infraction%20employees%20commit%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20majority%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20after%20an%20employee%20has%20hauled%20an%20employer%20into%20court%2C%20it%20is%20entirely%20reasonable%20for%20the%20employer%20to%20file%20its%20claims%20for%20minor%20infractions.%26quot%3B%20(Aday%20ultimately%20prevailed%20on%20the%20trade%20secret%20misappropriation%20allegations%2C%20because%20his%20employer%20couldn't%20prove%20he%20violated%20company%20policy.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobillard%2C%20the%20Oregon%20engineer%2C%20also%20accused%20his%20former%20employer%20Opal%20of%20retaliation%20after%20Opal's%20countersuit%20alleging%20trade%20secrets%20violations.%20His%20claim%20was%20dismissed%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20the%20court%20assumes%20a%20retaliatory%20motive%2C%20Plaintiff's%20retaliation%20claims%20fail%2C%26quot%3B%20Magistrate%20Judge%20John%20Acosta%20wrote%2C%20finding%20that%20Robillard%20had%20not%20proved%20the%20trade%20secret%20claims%20were%20baseless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20partner%20at%20Dhillon%20Law%20Group%20and%20head%20of%20the%20firm's%20employment%20law%20division%2C%20John-Paul%20Deol%20has%20sat%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20table.%20At%20times%2C%20he%20has%20defended%20employees%20against%20trade%20secrets%20counterclaims%2C%20and%20at%20times%20he%20had%20filed%20such%20claims%20on%20behalf%20of%20employers%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20huge%20piece%20of%20leverage%20over%20an%20employee%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20San%20Francisco%20attorney%20said.%20%26quot%3BOn%20the%20defense%20side%2C%20it's%20one%20of%20the%20first%20things%20you%20look%20at.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20multiple%20occasions%20when%20he's%20been%20preparing%20to%20file%20suit%20over%20workplace%20discrimination%2C%20a%20client's%20employer%20has%20threatened%20a%20trade%20secrets%20countersuit%2C%20he%20said.%20Sometimes%20that%20threat%20alone%20has%20been%20enough%20to%20prompt%20a%20worker%20to%20abandon%20their%20claim.%20The%20cost%20and%20reputational%20risk%20of%20defending%20against%20one%20of%20these%20claims%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20just%20too%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20dynamic%20is%20why%20it%20is%20so%20difficult%20to%20estimate%20the%20true%20impact%20of%20trade%20secrets%20law%20on%20workers%2C%20and%20how%20much%20it%20constrains%20their%20ability%20to%20speak%20out%20about%20wrongdoing.%20Multiple%20attorneys%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20mere%20suggestion%20of%20a%20trade%20secrets%20counterclaim%20had%20been%20enough%20to%20persuade%20workers%20to%20withdraw%20or%20settle%20their%20complaints.%20In%20addition%2C%20many%20trade%20secret%20cases%20may%20be%20litigated%20entirely%20in%20private%20arbitration%2C%20out%20of%20sight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20where%20the%20employee%20has%20a%20perfectly%20good%20defense%20to%20that%20claim%2C%20they%20know%20it's%20going%20to%20cost%20them%20money%20to%20fight%20it%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bachman%2C%20the%20Bethesda%20attorney.%20%26quot%3BIt%20does%20factor%20into%20their%20decision%20about%20whether%20or%20not%20to%20bring%20a%20case%20%E2%80%94%20or%20to%20settle%20it%20before%20they%20ever%20even%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20bring%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarl%20Boja%2C%20who'd%20worked%20as%20a%20salesperson%20near%20Akron%2C%20Ohio%2C%20brought%20a%20disability%20claim%20against%20a%20former%20employer%2C%20a%20roadside%20services%20firm%20called%20TA%2C%20related%20to%20his%20March%202024%20dismissal.%20In%20an%20interview%2C%20Moran%2C%20the%20Cleveland%20attorney%2C%20who%20represented%20Boja%2C%20said%20TA%20responded%20by%20telling%20him%20the%20company%20was%20preparing%20a%20trade%20secrets%20suit%20against%20his%20client%20over%20files%20Boja%20had%20emailed%20himself.%20If%20Boja%20would%20drop%20his%20claim%2C%20Moran%20recalled%2C%20TA%20would%20agree%20not%20to%20bring%20the%20case.%20(TA%20and%20its%20attorneys%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20didn't%20know%20that%20he%20was%20going%20to%20get%20fired%2C%26quot%3B%20Moran%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it's%20not%20as%20if%20he%20took%20these%20things%20and%20then%20quit%20and%20then%20formed%20a%20competitor.%26quot%3B%20Before%20Boja%20had%20time%20to%20consider%20the%20offer%2C%20Moran%20said%2C%20TA%20filed%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20mandatory%20arbitration%20agreement%20Boja%20had%20signed%20with%20TA%20as%20a%20condition%20of%20employment%20consigned%20his%20disability%20claim%20to%20private%20arbitration.%20But%20TA%20filed%20the%20trade%20secrets%20claim%20against%20him%20in%20open%20federal%20court%2C%20claiming%20he%20took%20the%20documents%20to%20a%20competitor%20%E2%80%94%20potentially%20risking%20Boja's%20reputation%20and%20future%20job%20opportunities.%20It%20also%20hurt%20him%20financially%3A%20Moran%20had%20agreed%20to%20represent%20Boja%20on%20contingency%20in%20the%20discrimination%20arbitration%2C%20but%20Boja%20is%20now%20paying%20him%20out-of-pocket%20to%20defend%20against%20the%20trade%20secrets%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDealing%20with%20TA's%20case%20against%20me%20has%20been%20emotionally%20difficult%2C%26quot%3B%20Boja%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20trouble%20sleeping%20or%20focusing%20on%20anything%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJerry%20Talton%20is%20also%20battling%20to%20save%20his%20reputation%20after%20being%20sued%20over%20document%20downloads.%20In%20October%202022%2C%20while%20employed%20as%20an%20executive%20at%20the%20fintech%20firm%20Carta%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20he%20wrote%20to%20the%20company's%20board%20of%20directors%20claiming%20a%20litany%20of%20wrongdoing%2C%20including%20bullying%20by%20senior%20executives%2C%20sexually%20inappropriate%20comments%20by%20colleagues%2C%20and%20employees%20failing%20to%20disclose%20financial%20conflicts%20of%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20before%20the%20company%20placed%20him%20on%20leave%20to%20investigate%2C%20Talton%20downloaded%20a%20raft%20of%20internal%20documents.%20An%20accidental%20email%20to%20the%20company's%20general%20counsel%20prompted%20a%20review%20of%20his%20IT%20activity%2C%20which%20surfaced%20the%20downloads.%20A%20filing%20Talton%20made%20in%20court%20said%20he'd%20offered%20to%20return%20the%20documents%20through%20counsel%2C%20but%20the%20company%20had%20declined%20and%20fired%20him%2C%20then%20filed%20suit%20claiming%20trade%20secret%20violations.%20Amanda%20Taggart%2C%20a%20Carta%20spokesperson%2C%20flatly%20denied%20that%20he'd%20offered%20to%20return%20the%20documents.%20Carta%20said%20in%20court%20filings%20that%20Talton%20had%20abused%20the%20company's%20trust%20and%20risked%20revealing%20business%20information%20it%20had%20spent%20years%20developing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECourt%20filings%20show%20that%20the%20litigation%20process%20agonizing%20for%20Talton.%20Carta%20unearthed%20salacious%20texts%20he%20had%20sent%20to%20sexual%20partners%20from%20company%20devices%20and%20made%20them%20public%20in%20court%20filings.%20%26quot%3BTalton%20became%20ridiculed%20around%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20his%20attorneys%20wrote%20in%20pursuing%20his%20ongoing%20counterclaims%20including%20retaliation%2C%20defamation%2C%20and%20wrongful%20discharge.%20%26quot%3BA%20good%20job%20offer%20was%20withdrawn.%20He%20has%20not%20been%20able%20to%20get%20another.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20easy%20to%20use%20these%20tools%20%E2%80%94%20that%20are%20there%20for%20a%20good%20reason%20%E2%80%94%20for%20purposes%20that%20are%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20Talton%20said%20in%20an%20interview.%20He%20described%20trade%20secrets%20laws%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20blunt%20weapon%26quot%3B%20that%20could%20be%20deployed%20against%20employees%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20you%20don't%20like%20their%20opinions%2C%20or%20you%20don't%20like%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20they've%20spoken%20up%20about%20what%20they've%20observed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20before%20Thanksgiving%20in%202020%2C%20the%20chief%20operating%20officer%20of%20a%20Harrisburg%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20debt%20collection%20firm%20slapped%20Nicole%20Durenleau%20across%20the%20face.%20She%20had%20previously%20reported%20inappropriate%20sexual%20comments%20and%20touching%20by%20the%20COO%2C%20Shell%20Sharma%2C%20to%20an%20employee%20relations%20representative%2C%20her%20attorney%20wrote%20in%20a%20court%20filing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurenleau%20left%20the%20company%2C%20NRA%20Group%2C%20in%20February%202021%20and%20promptly%20sent%20a%20demand%20letter%20complaining%20of%20sexual%20harassment%20and%20seeking%20back%20pay%20and%20compensation.%20She%20also%20reported%20Sharma%20to%20the%20police%20for%20striking%20her%2C%20and%20he%20was%20convicted%20of%20harassment%20that%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20counterattacked%2C%20suing%20her%20on%20hacking%20charges%20in%20April%2C%20and%20later%20added%20a%20trade%20secrets%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20claims%20hung%20on%20a%20thin%20thread.%20About%20a%20month%20before%20Durenleau%20quit%2C%20her%20manager%20requested%20a%20login%20credential%20for%20a%20website%20that%20tracks%20state%20licenses.%20Durenleau%20was%20out%20sick%20that%20day%2C%20so%20she%20asked%20a%20colleague%2C%20Jamie%20Badaczewski%2C%20to%20log%20into%20her%20account%20on%20NRA's%20computer%20network%20to%20find%20it.%20Badaczewski%20retrieved%20a%20spreadsheet%20of%20work%20logins%20Durenleau%20had%20created%20and%20sent%20it%20along%20to%20Durenleau's%20personal%20email%20address%20so%20she%20could%20share%20it%20with%20her%20manager.%20The%20company's%20attorneys%20asserted%20that%20creating%20the%20spreadsheet%20and%20having%20it%20sent%20to%20her%20personal%20email%20was%20trade%20secret%20misappropriation.%20The%20company%20sued%20Badaczewski%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20two%20years%20later%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20ruled%20that%20because%20passwords%20don't%20have%20%26quot%3Bindependent%20economic%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20they're%20not%20trade%20secrets.%20Counterclaims%20by%20Durenleau%20and%20Badaczewski%20alleging%20a%20hostile%20work%20environment%20and%20workplace%20retaliation%20remain%20ongoing%2C%20though%20Sharma%20died%20in%20early%202024.%20NRA%20Group%20has%20appealed%20the%20dismissal%20of%20the%20trade%20secrets%20claim%2C%20telling%20BI%20that%20the%20spreadsheet%20%26quot%3Bcontained%20highly%20sensitive%20trade%20secret%20information.%26quot%3B%20(Durenleau%20and%20Badaczewski's%20attorney%2C%20Cory%20Iannacone%2C%20said%20his%20clients%20had%20%26quot%3Balways%20maintained%20that%20NRA's%20claims%20were%20without%20merit%26quot%3B%20and%20would%20present%20their%20discrimination%20and%20retaliation%20claims%20at%20trial.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20spot%20illustration%20of%20a%20woman%20walking%20alone%20amongst%20a%20gavel.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67915e6810c98eace9138806%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETara%20Anand%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDefendants%20like%20Durenleau%20and%20Badaczewski%20who%20prevail%20when%20facing%20trade%20secrets%20claims%20will%20face%20headwinds%20if%20they%20seek%20to%20recoup%20their%20legal%20costs.%20The%20federal%20trade%20secrets%20law%20sets%20a%20high%20bar%20for%20defendants%20to%20be%20awarded%20fees%2C%20requiring%20the%20case%20to%20be%20brought%20in%20%26quot%3Bbad%20faith.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20judges%20sometimes%20find%20the%20evidence%20of%20trade%20secrets%20violations%20thin%2C%20they%20rarely%20find%20that%20the%20claims%20involved%20bad%20faith.%20In%20a%20recent%20case%20in%20California%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20called%20the%20case%20before%20her%20%26quot%3Bobjectively%20specious%2C%26quot%3B%20yet%20didn't%20approve%20the%20award%20of%20legal%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%3A%20Even%20when%20a%20company's%20trade%20secrets%20claim%20fails%2C%20it%20can%20exact%20financial%20harm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20any%20trade%20secret%20case%20that%20makes%20it%20all%20the%20way%20to%20trial%2C%20Seaman%2C%20the%20Washington%20and%20Lee%20professor%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYou're%20looking%20down%20the%20barrel%20of%20a%20million%20dollars%20or%20more%20in%20attorneys%20fees%20and%20expenses%2C%20and%20even%20if%20you%20win%2C%20no%20guarantee%20that%20you%20can%20get%20it%20back.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Robillard%2C%20the%20Oregon%20engineer%2C%20the%20legal%20process%20was%20grueling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20attempts%20to%20have%20the%20trade%20secrets%20claims%20against%20him%20dismissed%20through%20summary%20judgment%20failed.%20He%20sat%20for%20depositions%20and%20turned%20over%20reams%20of%20old%20files%20for%20discovery.%20He%20was%20fearful%20of%20talking%20about%20the%20case%20to%20anyone%20except%20his%20partner%2C%20concerned%20he'd%20be%20accused%20of%20another%20violation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20isolation%20is%20a%20big%20factor%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BParanoia%20is%20real%2C%20because%20you%20don't%20know%20who's%20looking%20or%20watching.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20he%20was%20fired%20from%20Opal%20Labs%2C%20he%20took%20on%20other%20technology%20jobs%20but%20found%20himself%20experiencing%20panic%20attacks%20and%20other%20symptoms%20of%20post-traumatic%20stress%20disorder.%20He%20left%20the%20tech%20sector%20in%202015%20and%20began%20training%20as%20a%20therapist%2C%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20trauma%20and%20relationship%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20parties%20finally%20reached%20a%20settlement%20in%20March%202021%2C%20just%20a%20few%20months%20before%20a%20trial%20was%20scheduled%20to%20begin.%20All%20claims%20were%20dismissed%20with%20prejudice.%20Opal%20agreed%20to%20pay%20a%20settlement%20of%20about%20%24220%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20understand%20that%20parties%20may%20have%20different%20recollections%20or%20perspectives%20on%20the%20events%20in%20question%2C%26quot%3B%20Colin%20Savoy%2C%20Opal's%20chief%20legal%20officer%2C%20wrote%20by%20email.%20%26quot%3BOpal%20remains%20confident%20in%20our%20actions%2C%20our%20defense%2C%20and%20our%20firm%20belief%20that%20the%20facts%20fully%20supported%20each%20and%20every%20defense%20and%20claim%20we%20presented.%20As%20a%20technol