lier%20worked%20as%20a%20doctor%20for%20the%20Pakistan%20Army.%20He%20had%20prior%20knowledge%20of%20the%20attacks%2C%20and%20a%20federal%20jury%20convicted%20him%20of%20helping%20Lashkar%20with%20material%20support%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fembed-player%2F%3Fid%3D893317%26category%3Dembed%26autostart%3D1%26pWidth%3D650%26pHeight%3D403%26embed_type%3Dstory%26mute%3D1%26autostart%3D1%26mutestart%3Dtrue%26ctitle%3D1%26miniplayer%3D1%26cache%3D2022%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20also%20known%20to%20Pakistani-American%20David%20Headley%2C%20who%20was%20among%20the%20main%20conspirators%20of%20the%2026%2F11%20attacks.%20Rana%20and%20Hadley%20were%20arrested%20in%202009%20by%20the%20FBI%20while%20plotting%20an%20attack%20against%20a%20Danish%20newspaper.%20During%20his%20interrogation%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Hadley%20had%20revealed%20before%20Indian%20officers%20that%20he%20had%20travelled%20to%20India%20five%20times%20between%202007%20and%202008%20and%20done%20recce%20for%20the%20Mumbai%20attacks%20-%20using%20a%20five-year%20visa%20that%20Rana%20had%20helped%20him%20obtain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHadley%20had%20also%20revealed%20the%20role%20of%20Lashkar%20in%20the%20Mumbai%20attacks%20and%20said%20he%20had%20opened%20an%20immigration%20company%20to%20hide%20his%20identity%20with%20Rana's%20help.%20He%20had%20testified%20that%20Rana%20gave%20him%20all%20the%20logistical%20and%20financial%20support%20he%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20prepare%20for%20the%20attack%2C%20Rana%20visited%20Mumbai%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20stayed%20at%20the%20Taj%20Mahal%20Hotel%2C%20which%20later%20became%20a%20target%20of%20the%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Extradition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20being%20legal%2C%20Rana's%20extradition%20has%20been%20a%20long%20diplomatic%20battle%20for%20India.%20In%202019%2C%20the%20government%20had%20first%20approached%20the%20US%20with%20a%20request%20to%20extradite%20him.%20For%20the%20next%20six%20years%2C%20India%20repeatedly%20followed%20this%20up%20with%20the%20US%20authorities%20while%20Rana%20looked%20for%20legal%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20breakthrough%20came%20last%20August%20when%20a%20lower%20court%20ordered%20his%20extradition%20and%20was%20upheld%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20earlier%20this%20month.%20It%20has%20now%20turned%20down%20a%20review%20request%2C%20clearing%20all%20the%20legal%20obstacles%20to%20his%20extradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fterrorists-to-economic-offenders-5-fugitives-india-is-trying-to-extradite-7554560%5C%22%3ETerrorists%20To%20Economic%20Offenders%3A%205%20Fugitives%20India%20Is%20Trying%20To%20Extradite%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202019%2C%20India%20has%20maintained%20Rana%20was%20the%20mastermind%20behind%20the%2026%2F11%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20defence%2C%20Rana%20had%20argued%20that%20he%20was%20tried%20in%20a%20local%20district%20court%20in%20Chicago%20for%20the%20Mumbai%20attacks%2C%20and%20he%20cannot%20be%20tried%20for%20the%20same%20offence%20in%20another%20country%20as%20per%20the%20extradition%20treaty%20between%20India%20and%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Solicitor%20General%2C%20however%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%20all%20the%20charges%20against%20Rana%2C%20on%20which%20India%20seeks%20his%20extradition%2C%20were%20not%20covered%20by%20the%20US%20government's%20prosecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20Next%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELegal%20obstacles%20being%20taken%20care%20of%2C%20it's%20now%20a%20matter%20of%20time%20before%20Rana%20is%20extradited%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20extradition%20will%20not%20be%20just%20a%20big%20diplomatic%20victory%20but%20an%20example%20of%20how%20people%20cannot%20run%20from%20the%20law%20after%20committing%20a%20crime.%20His%20interrogation%20on%20the%20Indian%20land%20will%20help%20Indian%20officers%20reveal%20new%20details%20and%20missing%20links.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERelated%20to%20the%2026%2F11%20attacks%20or%20not%2C%20cases%20can%20be%20reopened%20if%20the%20investigators%20find%20any%20clue%20from%20Rana.%20If%20someone%20evaded%20enforcement%20radar%20in%20the%20past%2C%20they%20could%20face%20a%20fresh%20probe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERana%20has%20been%20a%20close%20associate%20of%20the%20Pakistani%20spy%20agency%20ISI%20and%20by%20bringing%20him%20to%20India%2C%20Indian%20agencies%20will%20get%20access%20to%20what%20actually%20transpired%20behind%20this%20conspiracy%2C%20said%20PK%20Jain%2C%20former%20police%20chief%20of%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRana%20is%20aware%20of%20the%20operations%20of%20the%20ISI%20and%20Pakistani%20elements%20in%20America%20and%20India.%20He's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20storehouse%20of%20information.%20I'm%20sure%20Indian%20agencies%20will%20be%20able%20to%20dig%20out%20a%20lot%20of%20important%20information%20from%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAniket%20Nikam%2C%20an%20advocate%20at%20the%20Bombay%20High%20Court%2C%20said%20once%20Rana%20is%20brought%20back%2C%20a%20fresh%20case%20will%20be%20filed%20against%20him%20and%20a%20new%20chargesheet%20will%20be%20prepared.%20India%20and%20the%20US%20had%20signed%20an%20extradition%20treaty%20in%201998%2C%20under%20which%20the%20process%20of%20bringing%20him%20back%20had%20started%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20extradition%20process%20will%20start%20with%20Rana's%20deportation%20from%20the%20US.%20Indian%20officers%20will%20go%20there%20and%20take%20him%20into%20custody%2C%20after%20which%20he%20will%20face%20the%20trial%2C%20said%20Mr%20Nikam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20rejected%20Rana's%20appeal.%20After%20that%20you%20have%20no%20other%20option%20left.%20He%20will%20be%20brought%20to%20India.%20This%20victory%20was%20a